docs.lead_paragraph: SAO PAULO, Brazil, June 18 -- Governor Rockefeller told a group of Brazilian students today that he had raised the questions of press censorship, student arrests and political and academic freedom with President Arthur da Costa e Silva, head of the military-dominated Brazilian regime.
docs.abstract: Rockefeller tells 7 students, invited to meeting at US Embassy, Rio, that he raised questions of press censorship, student arrests and pol and acad freedom with Costa e Silva; students say they were able to describe to Rockefeller difficulties they face because of pol repression; emphasize they are not leaders; claim leaders are all in jail or hiding; student recalls Sen R F Kennedy '65 visit; Costa e Silva says halt in mil purchases from US since '64 necessitates re-equipment of Brazilian mil; Rockefeller flies to Sao Paulo; departure from Rio and arrival there are surrounded by rigorous mil security
